The paper deals with the algorithm selection task in the domain of Collaborative Filtering, which is a subfield of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed approach integrates subsampling landmarkers, a data characterization approach commonly used in Metalearning, with a Collaborative Filtering methodology, named CF4CF, which involves machine learning techniques such as matrix factorization and nearest neighbor methods. These techniques are also commonly used in the subfields of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of benchmark recommendation datasets, which are commonly used in the subfield of Data Science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of Collaborative Filtering, which is a subfield of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
